SIMPLE: bloodsucker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bloodsucker
<hw>Blood"suck`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any animal that sucks blood; esp., the leech
(<spn>Hirudo medicinalis</spn>), and related species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who sheds blood; a cruel, bloodthirsty man; one
guilty of bloodshed; a murderer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A hard and exacting master, landlord, or money
lender; an extortioner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bloodsucking</ent>⟦br⟧
